reviewText: This is the worst quality cartoon I have ever bought on Amazon. It was terrible. The voiceovers are horrendous the artwork sub par and the music is awful. I really don't have one good thing to say about this movie. My girls didn't seem to mind but for 7 bucks I would go buy something else, heck even if it was free I would go find something else.

reviewText: I rented this to watch with my granddaughter.  It dragged on and eventually  my granddaughter went off to play by herself instead of watching the rest of this video.  It has a decent story line, it is just is not well done.  There were pauses in the story almost as if they were spots to insert commercials.

reviewText: The animation for this is rather lackluster, but since it wasn't made for a full-length movie like Disney's classic, I suppose that can be forgiven, if not for the terrible storytelling and dialogue. I could barely make heads or tails of this and I've seen several different retellings of this story. If you're a fan of Hans Christian Andersen's story, this is one you definitely want to avoid.
